properties.name: as3_json
properties.description: • as3_json - (Required) Name of the of the Declarative AS3 JSON file

properties.name: tenant_name
properties.description: • tenant_name - (Required) This is the partition name where the application services will be configured.

properties.name: example.json
properties.description: • example.json - Example of AS3 Declarative JSON

{
   "class": "AS3",
   "action": "deploy",
   "persist": true,
   "declaration": {
      "class": "ADC",
      "schemaVersion": "3.0.0",
      "id": "urn:uuid:33045210-3ab8-4636-9b2a-c98d22ab915d",
      "label": "Sample 1",
      "remark": "Simple HTTP application with RR pool",
      "as3": {
         "class": "Tenant",
         "A1": {
            "class": "Application",
            "template": "http",
            "serviceMain": {
               "class": "Service_HTTP",
               "virtualAddresses": [
                  "10.0.1.10"
               ],
               "pool": "web_pool"
            },
            "web_pool": {
               "class": "Pool",
               "monitors": [
                  "http"
               ],
               "members": [{
                  "servicePort": 80,
                  "serverAddresses": [
                     "192.0.1.10",
                     "192.0.1.11"
                  ]
               }]
            }
         }
      }
   }
}

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name (Required) Name of the profile_fasthttp

properties.name: defaults_from
properties.description: • defaults_from - (Optional) Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

properties.name: connpoolidle_timeoutoverride
properties.description: • connpoolidle_timeoutoverride - (Optional) Specifies the number of seconds after which a server-side connection in a OneConnect pool is eligible for deletion, when the connection has no traffic.The value of this option overrides the idle-timeout value that you specify. The default value is 0 (zero) seconds, which disables the override setting.

properties.name: connpool_maxreuse
properties.description: • connpool_maxreuse - (Optional) Specifies the maximum number of times that the system can re-use a current connection. The default value is 0 (zero).

properties.name: connpool_maxsize
properties.description: • connpool_maxsize - (Optional) Specifies the maximum number of connections to a load balancing pool. A setting of 0 specifies that a pool can accept an unlimited number of connections. The default value is 2048.

properties.name: connpool_replenish
properties.description: • connpool_replenish - (Optional) The default value is enabled. When this option is enabled, the system replenishes the number of connections to a load balancing pool to the number of connections that existed when the server closed the connection to the pool. When disabled, the system replenishes the connection that was closed by the server, only when there are fewer connections to the pool than the number of connections set in the connpool-min-size connections option. Also see the connpool-min-size option..

properties.name: idle_timeout
properties.description: • idle_timeout - (Optional) Specifies an idle timeout in seconds. This setting specifies the number of seconds that a connection is idle before the connection is eligible for deletion.When you specify an idle timeout for the Fast L4 profile, the value must be greater than the bigdb database variable Pva.Scrub time in msec for it to work properly.The default value is 300 seconds.

properties.name: connpool_minsize
properties.description: • connpool_minsize - (Optional) Specifies the minimum number of connections to a load balancing pool. A setting of 0 specifies that there is no minimum. The default value is 10.

properties.name: connpool_step
properties.description: • connpool_step - (Optional) Specifies the increment in which the system makes additional connections available, when all available connections are in use. The default value is 4.

properties.name: forcehttp_10response
properties.description: • forcehttp_10response - (Optional) Specifies whether to rewrite the HTTP version in the status line of the server to HTTP 1.0 to discourage the client from pipelining or chunking data. The default value is disabled.

properties.name: maxheader_size
properties.description: • maxheader_size - (Optional) Specifies the maximum amount of HTTP header data that the system buffers before making a load balancing decision. The default setting is 32768.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name (Required) Name of the profile_fastl4

properties.name: defaults_from
properties.description: • defaults_from - (Optional) Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

properties.name: partition
properties.description: • partition - (Optional) Displays the administrative partition within which this profile resides

properties.name: client_timeout
properties.description: • client_timeout - (Optional) Specifies late binding client timeout in seconds. This setting specifies the number of seconds allowed for a client to transmit enough data to select a server when late binding is enabled. If it expires timeout-recovery mode will dictate what action to take.

properties.name: explicitflow_migration
properties.description: • explicitflow_migration - (Optional) Enables or disables late binding explicit flow migration that allows iRules to control when flows move from software to hardware. Explicit flow migration is disabled by default hence BIG-IP automatically migrates flows from software to hardware.

properties.name: hardware_syncookie
properties.description: • hardware_syncookie - (Optional) Enables or disables hardware SYN cookie support when PVA10 is present on the system. Note that when you set the hardware syncookie option to enabled, you may also want to set the following bigdb database variables using the "/sys modify db" command, based on your requirements: pva.SynCookies.Full.ConnectionThreshold (default: 500000), pva.SynCookies.Assist.ConnectionThreshold (default: 500000) pva.SynCookies.ClientWindow (default: 0). The default value is disabled.

properties.name: idle_timeout
properties.description: • idle_timeout - (Optional) Specifies an idle timeout in seconds. This setting specifies the number of seconds that a connection is idle before the connection is eligible for deletion.When you specify an idle timeout for the Fast L4 profile, the value must be greater than the bigdb database variable Pva.Scrub time in msec for it to work properly.The default value is 300 seconds.

properties.name: iptos_toclient
properties.description: • iptos_toclient - (Optional) Specifies an IP ToS number for the client side. This option specifies the Type of Service level that the traffic management system assigns to IP packets when sending them to clients. The default value is 65535 (pass-through), which indicates, do not modify.

properties.name: iptos_toserver
properties.description: • iptos_toserver - (Optional) Specifies an IP ToS number for the server side. This setting specifies the Type of Service level that the traffic management system assigns to IP packets when sending them to servers. The default value is 65535 (pass-through), which indicates, do not modify.

properties.name: keepalive_interval
properties.description: • keepalive_interval - (Optional) Specifies the keep alive probe interval, in seconds. The default value is disabled (0 seconds).

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name (Required) Name of the profile_http

properties.name: defaults_from
properties.description: • defaults_from - (Required) Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

properties.name: fallback_host
properties.description: • fallback_host - (Optional) Specifies an HTTP fallback host. HTTP redirection allows you to redirect HTTP traffic to another protocol identifier, host name, port number

properties.name: fallback_status_codes
properties.description: • fallback_status_codes - (Optional) Specifies one or more three-digit status codes that can be returned by an HTTP server.

properties.name: oneconnect_transformations
properties.description: • oneconnect_transformations - (Optional) Enables the system to perform HTTP header transformations for the purpose of keeping server-side connections open. This feature requires configuration of a OneConnect profile

properties.name: basic_auth_realm
properties.description: • basic_auth_realm - (Optional) Specifies a quoted string for the basic authentication realm. The system sends this string to a client whenever authorization fails. The default value is none

properties.name: head_insert
properties.description: • head_insert - (Optional) Specifies a quoted header string that you want to insert into an HTTP request

properties.name: insert_xforwarded_for
properties.description: • insert_xforwarded_for - (Optional) When using connection pooling, which allows clients to make use of other client requests' server-side connections, you can insert the X-Forwarded-For header and specify a client IP address

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name (Required) Name of the profile_http2

properties.name: defaults_from
properties.description: • defaults_from - (Required) Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

properties.name: concurrent_streams_per_connection
properties.description: • concurrent_streams_per_connection - (Optional) Specifies how many concurrent requests are allowed to be outstanding on a single HTTP/2 connection.

properties.name: connection_idle_timeout
properties.description: • connection_idle_timeout - (Optional) Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is idle before the connection is eligible for deletion..

properties.name: connpool_maxsize
properties.description: • connpool_maxsize - (Optional) Specifies the maximum number of connections to a load balancing pool. A setting of 0 specifies that a pool can accept an unlimited number of connections. The default value is 2048.

properties.name: activation_modes
properties.description: • activation_modes - (Optional) Specifies what will cause an incoming connection to be handled as a HTTP/2 connection. The default values npn and alpn specify that the TLS next-protocol-negotiation and application-layer-protocol-negotiation extensions will be used.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name (Required) Name of the profile_httpcompress

properties.name: defaults_from
properties.description: • defaults_from - (Optional) Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

properties.name: uri_exclude
properties.description: • uri_exclude - (Optional) Disables compression on a specified list of HTTP Request-URI responses. Use a regular expression to specify a list of URIs you do not want to compress.

properties.name: uri_include
properties.description: • uri_include - (Optional) Enables compression on a specified list of HTTP Request-URI responses. Use a regular expression to specify a list of URIs you want to compress.

properties.name: content_type_include
properties.description: • content_type_include - (Optional) Specifies a list of content types for compression of HTTP Content-Type responses. Use a string list to specify a list of content types you want to compress.

properties.name: content_type_exclude
properties.description: • content_type_exclude - (Optional) Excludes a specified list of content types from compression of HTTP Content-Type responses. Use a string list to specify a list of content types you want to compress.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name (Required) Name of the profile_oneconnect

properties.name: partition
properties.description: • partition - (Optional) Displays the administrative partition within which this profile resides

properties.name: defaults_from
properties.description: • defaults_from - (Optional) Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

properties.name: idle_timeout_override
properties.description: • idle_timeout_override - (Optional) Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is idle before the connection flow is eligible for deletion. Possible values are disabled, indefinite, or a numeric value that you specify. The default value is disabled.

properties.name: share_pools
properties.description: • share_pools - (Optional) Specify if you want to share the pool, default value is "disabled"

properties.name: max_age
properties.description: • max_age - (Optional) Specifies the maximum age in number of seconds allowed for a connection in the connection reuse pool. For any connection with an age higher than this value, the system removes that connection from the reuse pool. The default value is 86400.

properties.name: max_reuse
properties.description: • max_reuse - (Optional) Specifies the maximum number of times that a server-side connection can be reused. The default value is 1000.

properties.name: max_size
properties.description: • max_size - (Optional) Specifies the maximum number of connections that the system holds in the connection reuse pool. If the pool is already full, then the server-side connection closes after the response is completed. The default value is 10000.

properties.name: source_mask
properties.description: • source_mask - (Optional) Specifies a source IP mask. The default value is 0.0.0.0. The system applies the value of this option to the source address to determine its eligibility for reuse. A mask of 0.0.0.0 causes the system to share reused connections across all clients. A host mask (all 1's in binary), causes the system to share only those reused connections originating from the same client IP address.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name (Required) Name of the profile_tcp

properties.name: partition
properties.description: • partition - (Optional) Displays the administrative partition within which this profile resides

properties.name: defaults_from
properties.description: • defaults_from - (Optional) Specifies the profile that you want to use as the parent profile. Your new profile inherits all settings and values from the parent profile specified.

properties.name: idle_timeout
properties.description: • idle_timeout - (Optional) Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is idle before the connection is eligible for deletion. The default value is 300 seconds.

properties.name: close_wait_timeout
properties.description: • close_wait_timeout - (Optional) Specifies the number of seconds that a connection remains in a LAST-ACK state before quitting. A value of 0 represents a term of forever (or until the maxrtx of the FIN state). The default value is 5 seconds.

properties.name: finwait_timeout
properties.description: • finwait_timeout - (Optional) Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is in the FIN-WAIT-1 or closing state before quitting. The default value is 5 seconds. A value of 0 (zero) represents a term of forever (or until the maxrtx of the FIN state). You can also specify immediate or indefinite.

properties.name: finwait_2timeout
properties.description: • finwait_2timeout - (Optional) Specifies the number of seconds that a connection is in the FIN-WAIT-2 state before quitting. The default value is 300 seconds. A value of 0 (zero) represents a term of forever (or until the maxrtx of the FIN state).

properties.name: keepalive_interval
properties.description: • keepalive_interval - (Optional) Specifies the keep alive probe interval, in seconds. The default value is 1800 seconds.

properties.name: fast_open
properties.description: • fast_open - (Optional) When enabled, permits TCP Fast Open, allowing properly equipped TCP clients to send data with the SYN packet.

properties.name: deferred_accept
properties.description: • deferred_accept - (Optional) Specifies, when enabled, that the system defers allocation of the connection chain context until the client response is received. This option is useful for dealing with 3-way handshake DOS attacks. The default value is disabled.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) Name of the snat

properties.name: partition

properties.name: snatpool
properties.description: • snatpool - (Optional) Specifies the name of a SNAT pool. You can only use this option when automap and translation are not used.

properties.name: mirror
properties.description: • mirror - (Optional) Enables or disables mirroring of SNAT connections.

properties.name: autolasthop
properties.description: • autolasthop -(Optional) Specifies whether to automatically map last hop for pools or not. The default is to use next level's default.

properties.name: sourceport
properties.description: • sourceport - (Optional) Specifies whether the system preserves the source port of the connection. The default is preserve. Use of the preserve-strict setting should be restricted to UDP only under very special circumstances such as nPath or transparent (that is, no translation of any other L3/L4 field), where there is a 1:1 relationship between virtual IP addresses and node addresses, or when clustered multi-processing (CMP) is disabled. The change setting is useful for obfuscating internal network addresses.

properties.name: translation
properties.description: • translation - (Optional) Specifies the name of a translated IP address. Note that translated addresses are outside the traffic management system. You can only use this option when automap and snatpool are not used.

properties.name: vlansdisabled
properties.description: • vlansdisabled - (Optional) Disables the SNAT on all VLANs.

properties.name: vlans
properties.description: • vlans - (Optional) Specifies the name of the VLAN to which you want to assign the SNAT. The default is vlans-enabled.

properties.description: • mask - (Optional) Mask can either be in CIDR notation or decimal, i.e.: 24 or 255.255.255.0. A CIDR mask of 0 is the same as 0.0.0.0

properties.name: source_address_translation
properties.description: • source_address_translation - (Optional) Can be either omitted for none or the values automap or snat

properties.name: translate_address
properties.description: • translate_address - Enables or disables address translation for the virtual server. Turn address translation off for a virtual server if you want to use the virtual server to load balance connections to any address. This option is useful when the system is load balancing devices that have the same IP address.

properties.name: translate_port
properties.description: • translate_port - Enables or disables port translation. Turn port translation off for a virtual server if you want to use the virtual server to load balance connections to any service

properties.name: ip_protocol
properties.description: • ip_protocol- (Optional) Specify the IP protocol to use with the the virtual server (all, tcp, or udp are valid)

properties.name: server_profiles

properties.name: rules
properties.description: • rules - (Optional) The iRules you want run on this virtual server. iRules help automate the intercepting, processing, and routing of application traffic.

properties.name: vlans_disabled
properties.description: • vlans_disabled - (Optional Bool) Disables the virtual server on the VLANs specified by the VLANs option.

properties.description: • persistence_profiles - (Optional) List of persistence profiles associated with the Virtual Server.

properties.description: • fallback_persistence_profile - (Optional) Specifies a fallback persistence profile for the Virtual Server to use when the default persistence profile is not available.

properties.name: example-usage-of-json-file
properties.description: » Example Usage of Json file

{  
"fullPath":"/Common/simplehttp.app/simplehttp",
"generation":222,
